1
00:00:51,342 --> 00:00:54,637
CHARACTERS AND PLACES ASSOCIATED
IN THIS DRAMA ARE FICTIONAL

2
00:01:00,602 --> 00:01:01,728
Did you follow me home?

3
00:01:04,939 --> 00:01:07,317
-Are you nuts?
-Why do you keep changing your words?

4
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:09,152
Why?

5
00:01:10,904 --> 00:01:12,739
You told me to do everything by the book,

6
00:01:14,407 --> 00:01:16,576
but then reprimanded me for
being too by the book.

7
00:01:17,702 --> 00:01:20,205
Even today, the victim's life
comes before the evidence.

8
00:01:20,747 --> 00:01:23,541
He could've died
if we preserved the scene!

9
00:01:24,918 --> 00:01:26,544
Are you challenging me?

10
00:01:27,378 --> 00:01:28,379
What a nutjob.

11
00:01:32,926 --> 00:01:35,512
I'll be cut from the force anyway.

12
00:01:37,639 --> 00:01:39,307
I have nothing to lose.

13
00:01:40,725 --> 00:01:41,935
Mr. Oh Yang-chon.

14
00:02:03,915 --> 00:02:05,250
What's next?

15
00:02:07,293 --> 00:02:08,628
What comes after Mr. Oh Yang-chon?

16
00:02:09,295 --> 00:02:10,421
You grabbed me by my shirt.

17
00:02:11,422 --> 00:02:12,340
What will you do next?

18
00:02:17,512 --> 00:02:19,430
Next...

19
00:02:25,645 --> 00:02:27,188
You didn't think about it, right?

20
00:02:27,272 --> 00:02:28,857
You called my name and grabbed my shirt,

21
00:02:28,940 --> 00:02:30,441
but you didn't think further, right?

22
00:02:31,151 --> 00:02:32,277
You idiot.

23
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:33,736
You're so reckless.

24
00:02:33,820 --> 00:02:36,489
You just do things in a blind fury.

25
00:02:36,573 --> 00:02:37,907
What will you do next?

26
00:02:39,284 --> 00:02:42,495
Are you going to beat up a fellow cop?

27
00:02:42,745 --> 00:02:45,290
You scumbag!

28
00:02:49,544 --> 00:02:53,047
You remind me of a hairtail fish.
All you are is long. You idiot.

29
00:02:53,715 --> 00:02:56,467
Maybe I should just fry you up
and eat you.

30
00:02:57,719 --> 00:02:59,721
I can't believe you're my partner.

31
00:03:03,308 --> 00:03:04,851
Answer me before you leave.

32
00:03:05,727 --> 00:03:07,896
You should answer all my questions.

33
00:03:07,979 --> 00:03:09,522
I've got nothing to lose now.

34
00:03:14,611 --> 00:03:17,322
Why are you walking around
in the middle of the night?

35
00:03:17,864 --> 00:03:19,908
Take a cab if there's no bus.

36
00:03:20,950 --> 00:03:22,619
Did you walk for three hours

37
00:03:22,827 --> 00:03:23,912
from the hospital to here?

38
00:03:26,623 --> 00:03:27,707
Don't you have cab fare?

39
00:03:28,374 --> 00:03:29,792
Doesn't Jang-mi give you money?

40
00:03:34,797 --> 00:03:37,884
I'm talking to you.
Why aren't you answering me?

41
00:03:45,350 --> 00:03:47,435
Why are you still standing there? Go home!

42
00:03:53,316 --> 00:03:55,401
Are you still unaware of why

43
00:03:55,485 --> 00:03:57,278
you got such a low score?

44
00:03:58,613 --> 00:04:00,365
Is that it? Huh?

45
00:04:02,533 --> 00:04:03,993
Yes.

46
00:04:05,912 --> 00:04:06,913
Last Monday.

47
00:04:07,789 --> 00:04:10,291
Also, two weeks ago
on Tuesday, Wednesday, and Saturday.

48
00:04:11,501 --> 00:04:12,752
You were late for roll call

49
00:04:13,044 --> 00:04:14,796
by 5, 3, 7, and 4 minutes.

50
00:04:15,838 --> 00:04:16,923
Right?

51
00:04:17,090 --> 00:04:18,591
I wasn't late for work, but--

52
00:04:18,675 --> 00:04:20,969
Would it kill you to clean up the bathroom
after roll call?

53
00:04:21,052 --> 00:04:23,137
Who would do you harm?

54
00:04:23,429 --> 00:04:25,765
And when you caught the congressmen--

55
00:04:25,848 --> 00:04:29,310
I did as you said
and followed the DUI checkpoint manual.

56
00:04:29,394 --> 00:04:31,479
The congressmen refused
to take the sobriety test, so--

57
00:04:31,562 --> 00:04:34,565
So until then your score
wasn't good nor bad, it was average.

58
00:04:35,650 --> 00:04:37,902
You did a good job
and took care of things by the book.

59
00:04:38,861 --> 00:04:42,031
But what did you say to me
after arresting the congressmen?

60
00:04:42,115 --> 00:04:43,449
You said you were sorry.

61
00:04:44,659 --> 00:04:45,827
Are you stupid?

62
00:04:46,828 --> 00:04:48,955
You don't even know

63
00:04:49,372 --> 00:04:51,582
if you did something right or wrong.

64
00:04:52,792 --> 00:04:55,503
You just say you're sorry
without a sense of duty.

65
00:04:57,630 --> 00:04:59,924
So you,
who doesn't know his ass from his elbow,

66
00:05:00,925 --> 00:05:03,011
went from average back to poor.

67
00:05:04,345 --> 00:05:05,555
Do you understand now?

68
00:05:16,524 --> 00:05:17,900
He just says what he wants to say.

69
00:05:19,861 --> 00:05:22,488
I asked what was wrong with
saving someone before the evidence,

70
00:05:22,572 --> 00:05:23,865
but why didn't he answer me?

71
00:05:27,452 --> 00:05:29,871
I bet he has nothing to say.
Because I'm right.

72
00:05:33,082 --> 00:05:34,417
What an asshole.

73
00:05:36,044 --> 00:05:37,462
Tell me.

74
00:05:38,463 --> 00:05:41,132
Did you walk to and from the hospital
every day?

75
00:05:46,554 --> 00:05:47,555
Why did you buy hairtail?

76
00:05:49,057 --> 00:05:51,350
I remembered your mom used to like it,

77
00:05:51,434 --> 00:05:52,894
so when I saw it, I bought some.

78
00:05:54,729 --> 00:05:57,231
Since when did you care about...

79
00:05:57,315 --> 00:05:59,067
You shouldn't have beat her up back then.

80
00:06:09,535 --> 00:06:12,038
Hey, what are you doing?

81
00:06:12,121 --> 00:06:13,331
Can I stay the night?

82
00:06:14,540 --> 00:06:17,502
The last bus already left,
and there are no cabs in the area.

83
00:06:18,753 --> 00:06:20,755
It's too far to walk downtown,

84
00:06:21,089 --> 00:06:22,256
and it's cold.

85
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:24,967
Are we friends?

86
00:06:25,593 --> 00:06:26,928
We're not, but still.

87
00:06:27,929 --> 00:06:29,055
It's too cold.

88
00:06:30,556 --> 00:06:32,100
Let me stay just one night.

89
00:06:36,854 --> 00:06:39,190
I'm Lieutenant Oh Yang-chon's subordinate,
Yeom Sang-su.

90
00:06:44,612 --> 00:06:46,155
Please let me stay for one night.

91
00:06:46,405 --> 00:06:47,532
I can't get a ride home.

92
00:07:01,963 --> 00:07:05,174
No matter how much I think about it,
that kid is out of his mind.

93
00:07:05,967 --> 00:07:09,804
I've never seen a crazy jerk
like him before.

94
00:07:10,012 --> 00:07:12,014
What a nutjob.

95
00:07:18,771 --> 00:07:20,440
This is so annoying.

96
00:07:20,523 --> 00:07:23,943
Every day it's the same shit.
What the hell?

97
00:07:28,156 --> 00:07:30,992
All day I deal with drunk people
and give out parking tickets,

98
00:07:31,659 --> 00:07:34,704
and now I'm cleaning after
the drunk people after hours.

99
00:07:35,746 --> 00:07:37,206
Nothing's working out.

100
00:07:37,582 --> 00:07:39,876
Just mop it up
and finish it off with a dry rag.

101
00:07:41,711 --> 00:07:44,297
If a drunk person slips on the wet floor
while doing their business,

102
00:07:44,380 --> 00:07:46,424
you'll get your wish,
and we'll have a big accident.

103
00:07:46,507 --> 00:07:48,176
I can take care of it.

104
00:07:48,801 --> 00:07:50,928
Do you think I can't even clean up right?

105
00:07:53,264 --> 00:07:54,724
What are you looking at?

106
00:07:56,142 --> 00:07:58,060
You think you're the only smart one.

107
00:08:01,230 --> 00:08:05,151
Imagine if you had to deal with
an old mentor and drunk teenagers all day.

108
00:08:06,777 --> 00:08:08,821
Hey, if a domestic violence

109
00:08:08,905 --> 00:08:10,490
or disturbance case is reported,

110
00:08:10,573 --> 00:08:13,034
don't take the call before me, you bitch.

111
00:08:13,576 --> 00:08:16,913
Loyalty is about sharing big cases
or cases we can learn from.

112
00:08:16,996 --> 00:08:18,164
You just can't take them all.

113
00:08:20,082 --> 00:08:23,044
I'll apply for the Violent Crime Unit
after the probationary period.

114
00:08:23,544 --> 00:08:25,796
You only care about making good records.

115
00:08:25,922 --> 00:08:27,131
You're such a disloyal bitch.

116
00:08:37,099 --> 00:08:39,227
You can have the gift certificate
I got for working

117
00:08:40,645 --> 00:08:41,646
on the homicide case.

118
00:08:43,022 --> 00:08:44,732
What's your problem?

119
00:08:59,872 --> 00:09:00,873
A person

120
00:09:02,708 --> 00:09:03,709
died.

121
00:09:07,171 --> 00:09:08,839
She didn't just die.

122
00:09:10,591 --> 00:09:12,051
She got stabbed all over her body.

123
00:09:13,219 --> 00:09:15,054
There was blood all over her place,

124
00:09:15,846 --> 00:09:17,348
and her body was covered in blood.

125
00:09:19,684 --> 00:09:20,977
Do you really want to see that?

126
00:09:23,563 --> 00:09:25,231
Do you envy me that much
because I saw that?

127
00:09:30,945 --> 00:09:33,364
Dad! Dad...

128
00:09:36,158 --> 00:09:37,743
Dad...

129
00:09:37,827 --> 00:09:39,579
<i>Dad!</i>

130
00:09:41,414 --> 00:09:42,790
I've never seen

131
00:09:44,667 --> 00:09:46,669
anyone bleeding that much in my life.

132
00:09:49,338 --> 00:09:53,175
I know we learned at the academy
that such things happen

133
00:09:53,843 --> 00:09:55,845
around us all the time,

134
00:09:55,928 --> 00:09:57,471
but I thought they were just scaring us.

135
00:09:57,847 --> 00:10:00,308
I had no idea that I'd get to witness it
right before my eyes.

136
00:10:05,605 --> 00:10:06,689
Does such a brutal case

137
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:11,110
only appeal to you

138
00:10:13,362 --> 00:10:15,656
as a means to get more points
and a better review?

139
00:10:21,871 --> 00:10:23,706
You'd better not

140
00:10:25,041 --> 00:10:26,959
talk about performance or reviews

141
00:10:27,710 --> 00:10:30,379
in regard to a case where
someone got hurt or killed ever again.

142
00:10:31,964 --> 00:10:34,967
If you do, you'll get to see
how nasty and mean I can be, you bitch.

143
00:11:00,326 --> 00:11:04,872
EPISODE 5

144
00:11:26,227 --> 00:11:29,397
Hey, Jeong-o! Let's go home.

145
00:12:20,281 --> 00:12:24,076
<i>We provide services to remove keepsakes
left by the deceased. Don't worry.</i>

146
00:12:24,243 --> 00:12:26,245
<i>What if I see a ghost?
Will you get rid of it for me?</i>

147
00:12:29,457 --> 00:12:32,251
My dad will wake up. Just leave it on.

148
00:12:32,334 --> 00:12:34,336
<i>What's the point of living
if you're going to die?</i>

149
00:12:35,463 --> 00:12:36,464
<i>Take this.</i>

150
00:12:45,848 --> 00:12:47,308
AWARD FOR ACHIEVEMENT

151
00:12:50,186 --> 00:12:51,228
You've received an award.

152
00:12:51,395 --> 00:12:53,230
I've received more than one.

153
00:12:58,277 --> 00:13:00,237
My favorite part of the police charter

154
00:13:00,988 --> 00:13:04,074
is the line about how
it's the police's duty to protect the life

155
00:13:04,158 --> 00:13:06,952
and property of every citizen.

156
00:13:08,913 --> 00:13:10,873
What kind of nonsense
will you spew this time?

157
00:13:11,290 --> 00:13:14,084
Why are you talking about the charter
in the middle of the night?

158
00:13:16,587 --> 00:13:17,630
About what happened today,

159
00:13:19,381 --> 00:13:23,511
I prioritized life over evidence.
What's wrong with that?

160
00:13:27,890 --> 00:13:30,476
How can evidence come before life?
Do you think it's right?

161
00:13:31,477 --> 00:13:34,438
No one complimented me
even though I saved someone's life,

162
00:13:35,356 --> 00:13:37,233
and you're not even talking to me.

163
00:13:37,775 --> 00:13:39,860
The captain of the forensics team
even hit you.

164
00:13:40,444 --> 00:13:42,696
I deserved that slap in the face.

165
00:13:47,201 --> 00:13:50,204
We must move with a partner
in emergencies, but I ignored that rule.

166
00:13:51,247 --> 00:13:54,625
I was like, "You do whatever you want.
I'll do the same."

167
00:13:57,336 --> 00:14:00,589
No matter how stupid your partner seems,
a partner is still a partner.

168
00:14:02,508 --> 00:14:04,176
It was my fault for ignoring you.

169
00:14:06,971 --> 00:14:08,097
Had you called me

170
00:14:09,098 --> 00:14:11,392
when you heard the victim
moaning in pain in the restroom...

171
00:14:12,434 --> 00:14:14,228
Had I ordered you to do so,

172
00:14:15,187 --> 00:14:17,606
you would've saved a life,
and I would've gotten the evidence.

173
00:14:18,190 --> 00:14:19,984
We would've killed two birds
with one stone

174
00:14:20,192 --> 00:14:22,444
and finished everything exactly
according to the manual.

175
00:14:23,195 --> 00:14:24,363
Don't you think so?

176
00:14:31,620 --> 00:14:32,663
You're right.

177
00:14:40,087 --> 00:14:41,922
There's no such thing as a stupid mentee.

178
00:14:43,132 --> 00:14:46,260
We should always blame their dumb mentors
who didn't teach them right.

179
00:14:47,970 --> 00:14:49,972
Hence, everything that happened today
is my fault,

180
00:14:50,973 --> 00:14:52,391
your dumb mentor.

181
00:14:59,148 --> 00:15:00,900
But now that we're a team...

182
00:15:02,401 --> 00:15:03,485
Are we going to be okay?

183
00:15:04,778 --> 00:15:06,739
I think I'm in deep shit.

184
00:15:12,286 --> 00:15:13,287
I feel the same way.

185
00:15:13,913 --> 00:15:14,788
You little...

186
00:15:16,457 --> 00:15:18,125
Why are you laughing?

187
00:15:29,887 --> 00:15:31,388
By the way, I heard you were married.

188
00:15:32,598 --> 00:15:34,725
But why do you live with your father,
not your family?

189
00:16:37,287 --> 00:16:38,539
<i>I knew you'd be here.</i>

190
00:17:00,978 --> 00:17:01,979
<i>Why do you look so upset?</i>

191
00:17:03,397 --> 00:17:04,440
<i>Did something happen?</i>

192
00:17:09,486 --> 00:17:11,113
<i>Hey, I actually...</i>

193
00:17:13,615 --> 00:17:14,992
Don't go to the hospital today.

194
00:17:18,203 --> 00:17:19,663
Your legs hurt, right?

195
00:17:19,830 --> 00:17:21,457
No, they're fine.

196
00:17:21,540 --> 00:17:24,084
Then why do you have pain relief patches
all over your body?

197
00:17:25,544 --> 00:17:27,713
Why do you have to walk
for five to six hours

198
00:17:27,796 --> 00:17:30,758
to the hospital and back every single day?
It's so bad for your knees.

199
00:17:31,675 --> 00:17:33,135
<i>She'd never do that.</i>

200
00:17:33,427 --> 00:17:36,305
Take a taxi or the bus
if you want to go to the hospital today.

201
00:17:36,638 --> 00:17:37,639
Okay?

202
00:17:39,391 --> 00:17:40,642
Okay?

203
00:17:41,393 --> 00:17:42,394
<i>Really?</i>

204
00:17:43,145 --> 00:17:45,189
<i>You really didn't see anything?</i>

205
00:17:45,272 --> 00:17:46,857
Gosh, seriously.

206
00:17:48,942 --> 00:17:50,736
Don't go to the hospital today, okay?

207
00:17:51,361 --> 00:17:53,781
If you can't walk because
your knees get all messed up,

208
00:17:53,864 --> 00:17:56,075
Jang-mi and I'll have to suffer
while taking care of you!

209
00:17:59,119 --> 00:18:01,163
Since when were you so good to Mom?

210
00:18:03,123 --> 00:18:04,792
Do you know why I became a cop?

211
00:18:05,709 --> 00:18:08,128
To lock up men like you
who beat up other people.

212
00:18:18,263 --> 00:18:19,765
You used to beat her up while drunk.

213
00:18:22,267 --> 00:18:25,145
What's the point of being good to her now
when she's going to die soon?

214
00:18:25,646 --> 00:18:28,148
What's the point of buying hairtail fish?

215
00:18:39,660 --> 00:18:42,246
I told you not to buy the farm.
Why did you buy it?

216
00:18:43,413 --> 00:18:45,290
If you hadn't,

217
00:18:45,457 --> 00:18:47,918
she wouldn't have collapsed
while picking weeds in the sun!

218
00:18:49,419 --> 00:18:51,922
What kind of man talks so much

219
00:18:52,131 --> 00:18:53,590
in front of the dining table?

220
00:18:53,924 --> 00:18:55,592
You're so full of shit.

221
00:19:39,553 --> 00:19:40,721
Goodbye!

222
00:19:41,847 --> 00:19:43,140
I'm sorry I'm late.

223
00:19:43,223 --> 00:19:45,434
There were too many people
at the doctor's. You should go.

224
00:19:45,517 --> 00:19:47,644
Next time, come on your day off,
not on a day you work.

225
00:19:47,728 --> 00:19:49,605
If you did a good job, I wouldn't come.

226
00:19:49,813 --> 00:19:51,940
I'm exhausted from working,
but I come here from Seoul.

227
00:20:00,699 --> 00:20:02,868
Also, clean the kitchen whenever you can.

228
00:20:02,951 --> 00:20:04,828
It's always a mess.

229
00:20:04,953 --> 00:20:08,415
I come here after a long day's work,
and I have to work again. It's exhausting.

230
00:20:08,957 --> 00:20:10,918
Just quit if it's that exhausting.

231
00:20:11,585 --> 00:20:13,378
Why are you bragging anyway?

232
00:20:13,462 --> 00:20:16,715
What's so exhausting about
a job so many people do?

233
00:20:16,798 --> 00:20:18,342
Even your sick mother is working.

234
00:20:18,508 --> 00:20:20,969
So if you're exhausted, just quit already!

235
00:20:39,863 --> 00:20:41,698
What if I quit because it's exhausting?

236
00:20:43,033 --> 00:20:45,535
Can you pay back the loan
for the coffee shop?

237
00:20:46,870 --> 00:20:48,372
A job like everyone else's?

238
00:20:50,040 --> 00:20:52,501
Aside from cops,
who else sees dead people?

239
00:20:54,461 --> 00:20:57,047
Do you have any idea how grueling that is?

240
00:21:04,846 --> 00:21:08,517
She always seems irritated these days.

241
00:21:08,892 --> 00:21:11,353
It's not like she earns a lot anyway.

242
00:21:17,734 --> 00:21:19,278
<i>It's not my place to speak,</i>

243
00:21:19,778 --> 00:21:22,698
-but your father--
-Don't speak if it's not your place.

244
00:21:23,031 --> 00:21:24,741
You are too harsh on your father.

245
00:21:24,825 --> 00:21:27,119
Stay out of it
and be good to your own father.

246
00:21:27,703 --> 00:21:29,121
I don't have a father to treat well.

247
00:21:33,542 --> 00:21:34,459
He passed away.

248
00:21:39,965 --> 00:21:41,216
How did he pass away?

249
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:43,635
He would still be young if he were alive.

250
00:21:44,094 --> 00:21:45,470
It was a hit-and-run.

251
00:21:46,430 --> 00:21:48,974
The killer was caught, and it was a cop.

252
00:21:50,559 --> 00:21:51,601
Funny, right?

253
00:21:52,811 --> 00:21:54,021
Is that true?

254
00:22:00,402 --> 00:22:02,029
I'm asking because I'm worried.

255
00:22:03,071 --> 00:22:04,573
Did you join the force

256
00:22:05,574 --> 00:22:07,200
to get back at the police?

257
00:22:20,047 --> 00:22:21,923
Why are you breathing so heavily?

258
00:22:22,007 --> 00:22:22,841
Do you have asthma?

259
00:22:29,890 --> 00:22:30,932
You should rest.

260
00:22:32,100 --> 00:22:33,769
I'll rest when I want to.

261
00:22:48,950 --> 00:22:50,577
Talk about useless pride.

262
00:22:56,750 --> 00:22:57,667
I really hate him.

263
00:23:04,591 --> 00:23:07,761
Yang-chon, did you know five years ago,
Lieutenant Lee said he wanted

264
00:23:07,969 --> 00:23:09,429
to go to the Violent Crime Unit.

265
00:23:09,513 --> 00:23:11,598
I told him not to because he was too old.

266
00:23:13,058 --> 00:23:14,518
I know that's why he's like that.

267
00:23:16,978 --> 00:23:18,980
You and Han-sol are ridiculous too.

268
00:23:21,233 --> 00:23:22,734
Hongil Division is notorious

269
00:23:22,859 --> 00:23:25,195
for being one of the most difficult
divisions around,

270
00:23:25,654 --> 00:23:27,614
so why would you accept him?

271
00:23:27,781 --> 00:23:29,616
You should've sent him to
the quiet countryside.

272
00:23:30,158 --> 00:23:32,577
What if that old man breaks a few bones
or gets hurt?

273
00:23:32,661 --> 00:23:34,371
Will you take responsibility for that?

274
00:23:34,454 --> 00:23:36,540
Why would I have to do that?

275
00:23:36,706 --> 00:23:40,669
He's more than equipped
to take care of himself.

276
00:23:40,961 --> 00:23:42,087
Isn't that right?

277
00:23:44,005 --> 00:23:45,841
Has my old age ever got in the way

278
00:23:45,924 --> 00:23:48,009
of you or this division?

279
00:23:48,885 --> 00:23:50,512
Do you think you'll stay young forever?

280
00:23:50,595 --> 00:23:51,763
Come on.

281
00:23:52,305 --> 00:23:54,099
You were my first mentor.

282
00:23:54,266 --> 00:23:56,268
I'm just worried about you,

283
00:23:56,852 --> 00:23:58,812
and I want you to stay safe.

284
00:23:58,895 --> 00:24:00,522
Stay out of my life.

285
00:24:01,189 --> 00:24:03,233
I couldn't care less about
your good intentions.

286
00:24:10,991 --> 00:24:12,492
Lieutenant Lee isn't doing great.

287
00:24:13,326 --> 00:24:14,786
He's retiring soon,

288
00:24:14,870 --> 00:24:16,580
and his son divorced recently.

289
00:24:17,455 --> 00:24:18,957
Those who retire are said to be

290
00:24:19,124 --> 00:24:20,750
just as stressed as those with cancer.

291
00:24:20,834 --> 00:24:21,710
Try to understand.

292
00:24:24,838 --> 00:24:27,883
This taser gun,
when used according to the manual,

293
00:24:27,966 --> 00:24:29,843
will ensure the safety

294
00:24:29,926 --> 00:24:32,679
of the people and the police
in the safest way possible.

295
00:24:32,846 --> 00:24:35,849
The safest parts of the body
to use the taser gun are...

296
00:24:36,850 --> 00:24:39,728
You must refrain from shooting
the taser gun at the heart, head, face,

297
00:24:40,353 --> 00:24:41,688
and genitals.

298
00:24:41,771 --> 00:24:43,023
Shoot towards the arms and legs.

299
00:24:43,106 --> 00:24:44,441
Repeat!

300
00:24:44,524 --> 00:24:47,027
"You must refrain from shooting
the taser gun at the heart, head,

301
00:24:47,110 --> 00:24:48,570
face, and genitals.

302
00:24:48,653 --> 00:24:50,655
Shoot towards the arms and legs."

303
00:24:51,198 --> 00:24:53,116
The range of this taser gun

304
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:55,243
-is 6.5m.
-Are you still mad at me?

305
00:24:55,869 --> 00:24:57,871
Do I look like I have to time
to focus on you?

306
00:24:57,954 --> 00:24:59,664
Be aware of the range at all times.

307
00:24:59,831 --> 00:25:02,042
In order to use the taser gun properly,

308
00:25:02,125 --> 00:25:04,753
the most important thing
is target practice.

309
00:25:04,836 --> 00:25:06,421
How can we practice often?

310
00:25:06,546 --> 00:25:07,881
We're tired as it is.

311
00:25:07,964 --> 00:25:10,634
-Practice with a BB gun at home then.
-Pop, pop.

312
00:25:11,968 --> 00:25:13,762
Stop it!

313
00:25:14,095 --> 00:25:15,013
Sorry.

314
00:25:16,264 --> 00:25:17,891
Regardless of whether we're exhausted,

315
00:25:18,016 --> 00:25:19,726
or we need to travel far to practice

316
00:25:19,809 --> 00:25:21,728
because there aren't any shooting ranges
near us,

317
00:25:21,853 --> 00:25:24,773
-if there's an accident--
-Whether we were after a culprit

318
00:25:24,856 --> 00:25:26,399
or on the job,

319
00:25:26,942 --> 00:25:28,735
our country won't protect us.

320
00:25:29,236 --> 00:25:30,195
It's all on us.

321
00:25:30,820 --> 00:25:33,740
So stop complaining,
cut back on sleeping, and spend your money

322
00:25:33,823 --> 00:25:35,951
to practice at the shooting range. Got it?

323
00:25:36,534 --> 00:25:37,410
-Yes, sir!
-Yes, sir!

324
00:25:37,953 --> 00:25:38,954
Your superiors are right.

325
00:25:39,037 --> 00:25:42,249
Our country won't look out for us.
We must protect ourselves.

326
00:25:42,332 --> 00:25:45,835
So stay focused
and use the taser with care.

327
00:25:45,919 --> 00:25:47,087
-Yes, sir!
-Yes, sir!

328
00:25:47,170 --> 00:25:48,255
Lastly...

329
00:25:48,838 --> 00:25:49,923
The taser must not be used

330
00:25:50,006 --> 00:25:53,718
on pregnant women or children under 14.

331
00:25:53,802 --> 00:25:54,970
Repeat!

332
00:25:55,053 --> 00:25:58,431
"Don't use a taser gun on a pregnant woman
or children under 14."

333
00:25:58,515 --> 00:26:00,100
HONGIL PATROL DIVISION

334
00:26:01,726 --> 00:26:03,144
How can we help you?

335
00:26:05,021 --> 00:26:06,147
Ma'am!

336
00:26:07,232 --> 00:26:08,984
What brings you here?

337
00:26:09,067 --> 00:26:10,443
Please have a seat.

338
00:26:11,027 --> 00:26:13,530
My gosh! You haven't been acknowledged us

339
00:26:13,613 --> 00:26:17,200
even if we bump into each other,
so I thought you had forgotten about us.

340
00:26:17,742 --> 00:26:19,744
So what brings you here?

341
00:26:19,828 --> 00:26:22,372
No reason. I just wanted to see you.

342
00:26:22,956 --> 00:26:24,165
Goodness.

343
00:26:25,834 --> 00:26:26,835
Ma'am!

344
00:26:28,253 --> 00:26:31,673
You shouldn't have.
I bet it was expensive.

345
00:26:31,756 --> 00:26:32,757
Who are you?

346
00:26:37,512 --> 00:26:38,847
It's only for you.

347
00:26:41,516 --> 00:26:44,853
Ma'am, it's Lieutenant Lee Sam-bo.

348
00:26:45,395 --> 00:26:47,188
Don't you remember me?

349
00:26:47,272 --> 00:26:49,941
We said hi on the streets a few days ago.

350
00:26:50,025 --> 00:26:51,192
It's Sam-bo.

351
00:26:52,235 --> 00:26:54,404
About 20 years ago,
Han-sol and I carried Han-soon.

352
00:26:54,946 --> 00:26:57,198
Nothing happened to my Han-soon.

353
00:26:57,282 --> 00:26:59,743
Nothing bad happened to her.

354
00:26:59,826 --> 00:27:01,369
Who are you

355
00:27:01,453 --> 00:27:03,997
to speak of my Han-soon?

356
00:27:04,080 --> 00:27:05,123
You jerk.

357
00:27:08,043 --> 00:27:09,085
Ma'am?

358
00:27:09,502 --> 00:27:10,795
Ma'am.

359
00:27:11,296 --> 00:27:12,422
Ma'am!

360
00:27:14,341 --> 00:27:16,926
What's going on? Who is she?

361
00:27:18,053 --> 00:27:21,014
Oh, her.

362
00:27:22,515 --> 00:27:23,850
About 20 years ago,

363
00:27:25,018 --> 00:27:26,519
when Han-sol and I were here,

364
00:27:27,062 --> 00:27:31,441
there was a case where a stepfather
sexually assaulted his stepdaughter.

365
00:27:32,400 --> 00:27:34,277
The mother witnessed it,

366
00:27:34,361 --> 00:27:36,654
and the two of them drank cleaning bleach.

367
00:27:37,322 --> 00:27:39,699
The landlord called, and we went over.

368
00:27:39,783 --> 00:27:42,452
The lady you just saw was the mom.

369
00:27:43,495 --> 00:27:45,121
Oh, my goodness.

370
00:27:46,039 --> 00:27:47,749
Why doesn't she recognize me?

371
00:27:47,832 --> 00:27:49,084
Obang Junction, Sungwon-gil 27.

372
00:27:49,167 --> 00:27:52,003
A mother in her 30s has collapsed
at Speed Internet Cafe.

373
00:27:52,087 --> 00:27:53,755
<i>The child is alone.</i>

374
00:27:53,838 --> 00:27:55,256
<i>Obang Junction, Sungwon-gil 27.</i>

