384
00:28:36,965 --> 00:28:37,966
Is it tasty?

385
00:28:38,717 --> 00:28:40,468
Give me one.

386
00:28:43,972 --> 00:28:46,057
It's so tasty.

387
00:28:53,231 --> 00:28:56,359
ANGEL JU-YEON, LEVEL 39

388
00:28:57,569 --> 00:28:58,820
Captain An.

389
00:29:02,115 --> 00:29:04,033
Lieutenant Oh Yang-chon
wants to see you outside.

390
00:29:07,787 --> 00:29:09,122
Stay close to the child.

391
00:29:11,166 --> 00:29:14,669
Take photos of everything here,
both as a whole and close up.

392
00:29:14,753 --> 00:29:16,045
Yes, ma'am.

393
00:29:22,343 --> 00:29:23,219
You can have it.

394
00:29:41,154 --> 00:29:42,530
BAREUN PHARMACY

395
00:29:43,323 --> 00:29:46,034
PRESCRIPTION, CHO HYE-EUN

396
00:29:48,620 --> 00:29:50,079
Thank you for your cooperation.

397
00:30:02,258 --> 00:30:05,011
I sent you everything I got
from the part-timer.

398
00:30:06,095 --> 00:30:08,515
The woman practically lived here
for almost ten months.

399
00:30:08,681 --> 00:30:10,683
She lives in the study room
behind this building.

400
00:30:11,267 --> 00:30:12,393
She has depression.

401
00:30:13,561 --> 00:30:15,104
The bag was full of pills.

402
00:30:15,188 --> 00:30:17,524
She filled the prescription
and didn't take any.

403
00:30:19,067 --> 00:30:20,819
Where did she get the money to live on?

404
00:30:20,902 --> 00:30:23,571
I saw her prescription,
and it cost her 500 won.

405
00:30:24,280 --> 00:30:25,990
She's on welfare.

406
00:30:32,330 --> 00:30:34,666
I checked the kid as soon as I arrived.

407
00:30:35,333 --> 00:30:36,417
He has severe atopy.

408
00:30:36,960 --> 00:30:39,420
He didn't get abused by his mom, but...

409
00:30:45,718 --> 00:30:47,136
He wants to pee.

410
00:30:53,434 --> 00:30:56,145
The problem is, he wasn't treated

411
00:30:57,188 --> 00:30:59,607
and was neglected for a long time.

412
00:31:00,233 --> 00:31:04,571
The mom named her online character
Ju-yeon, after the kid.

413
00:31:05,196 --> 00:31:08,408
She abandoned him in reality
and cared for him online.

414
00:31:09,200 --> 00:31:10,201
That's escapism.

415
00:31:11,369 --> 00:31:12,787
Neglect is abuse too.

416
00:31:13,371 --> 00:31:16,499
-Neglect is abuse.
-Mister, I finished peeing.

417
00:31:23,047 --> 00:31:24,257
Let's wash your hands.

418
00:31:34,726 --> 00:31:36,603
We must send the kid to a facility.

419
00:31:37,061 --> 00:31:39,772
I called one. Someone should be here soon.

420
00:31:50,825 --> 00:31:51,743
So,

421
00:31:53,161 --> 00:31:54,579
how long are we going to do this?

422
00:31:55,413 --> 00:31:56,831
It's awkward and annoying.

423
00:31:58,333 --> 00:32:00,501
Let's end the awkward and annoying bit.

424
00:32:03,338 --> 00:32:04,213
Let's get divorced.

425
00:32:04,881 --> 00:32:07,425
How can you say that
outside the bathroom of a crime scene?

426
00:32:14,140 --> 00:32:15,224
Fine.

427
00:32:15,725 --> 00:32:17,143
Let's meet when I'm off duty.

428
00:32:18,436 --> 00:32:19,479
Let's meet and...

429
00:32:20,647 --> 00:32:23,566
Fine, we'll get divorced or... Damn...

430
00:32:24,609 --> 00:32:27,403
-We can go on living separately--
-The officer from the facility is here.

431
00:32:27,487 --> 00:32:30,573
Go to the study room and pack
what the mom and child might need.

432
00:32:31,699 --> 00:32:33,117
Hi, this is An Jang-mi.

433
00:32:33,576 --> 00:32:34,577
Yes.

434
00:32:34,827 --> 00:32:36,162
Come into the Internet cafe.

435
00:32:36,245 --> 00:32:37,455
I'll call when I'm off duty.

436
00:32:38,498 --> 00:32:39,791
Let's spend a long time together.

437
00:32:40,375 --> 00:32:41,793
Let's eat and have tea.

438
00:32:45,296 --> 00:32:46,589
The officer from the facility--

439
00:32:46,673 --> 00:32:49,300
Is almost here. I heard from the bathroom.

440
00:32:54,263 --> 00:32:57,225
Did you hear my wife
ask me for a divorce too?

441
00:33:13,741 --> 00:33:16,786
Gosh. She collected her medication
instead of taking them.

442
00:33:17,787 --> 00:33:18,830
It's so annoying.

443
00:33:19,872 --> 00:33:22,375
In the end, the law will probably
let her off with probation.

444
00:33:23,167 --> 00:33:24,877
Then the kid will continue
being neglected.

445
00:33:25,837 --> 00:33:27,964
How is neglect different from violence?

446
00:33:29,382 --> 00:33:30,383
Our country sucks.

447
00:33:30,967 --> 00:33:32,677
It's only great for the adults.

448
00:33:33,803 --> 00:33:36,014
What mom neglects her kid to play games?

449
00:33:36,097 --> 00:33:37,849
What kind of a bitch does that?

450
00:33:38,641 --> 00:33:41,019
If she can't raise him,
send him to an orphanage.

451
00:33:41,102 --> 00:33:42,186
Don't talk.

452
00:33:42,478 --> 00:33:44,647
Your voice is getting into the video.

453
00:33:46,399 --> 00:33:49,193
What was that? Did you say
she should send her kid to an orphanage?

454
00:33:49,277 --> 00:33:50,737
Whether the parents are good or bad,

455
00:33:50,820 --> 00:33:52,572
living with them
is better than being at an--

456
00:33:52,655 --> 00:33:55,491
Would a kid who barely
gets to eat feel the same?

457
00:34:04,208 --> 00:34:05,251
What's up with him?

458
00:34:15,219 --> 00:34:17,513
What's this?
She kept her sleeping pills separately.

459
00:34:19,724 --> 00:34:21,809
If we were late,
this could've been really bad.

460
00:34:42,288 --> 00:34:43,372
Hello.

461
00:34:43,498 --> 00:34:45,416
The passenger isn't wearing her seatbelt,

462
00:34:45,500 --> 00:34:47,668
and you watched TV as you were driving.

463
00:34:47,794 --> 00:34:49,962
I forgot. Could you let us off this once?

464
00:34:50,129 --> 00:34:51,172
Please show me your ID.

465
00:34:51,380 --> 00:34:54,550
-You didn't have your seatbelt on?
-I didn't realize. I forgot.

466
00:35:07,980 --> 00:35:10,358
We'll be on standby here today.

467
00:35:10,983 --> 00:35:13,069
A team requested assistance
with a drunk at a--

468
00:35:13,152 --> 00:35:14,403
Are you in charge?

469
00:35:17,281 --> 00:35:18,866
Today, we will be on standby here.

470
00:35:20,493 --> 00:35:21,536
This is work too.

471
00:35:21,619 --> 00:35:23,955
Murder and violence crimes
isn't the only kind of work.

472
00:35:24,497 --> 00:35:25,957
This is being productive too.

473
00:35:32,421 --> 00:35:33,589
Did you see them?

474
00:35:33,798 --> 00:35:36,592
See? They're going to take care of
the convenience store drunk.

475
00:35:42,098 --> 00:35:44,392
He has a few screws loose.

476
00:35:44,475 --> 00:35:46,185
He keeps staring at his phone.

477
00:35:46,269 --> 00:35:49,605
He asked to go to Dohwa 1-dong's
Community Center, so I took him there.

478
00:35:49,689 --> 00:35:51,607
But he wouldn't get out,
nor would he pay me.

479
00:35:51,691 --> 00:35:52,859
Then he suddenly cursed

480
00:35:52,942 --> 00:35:55,695
and even spit at me.

481
00:36:06,747 --> 00:36:10,334
Sir, get out of the taxi.

482
00:36:10,877 --> 00:36:14,297
You didn't pay your fare,
and you refuse to get out.

483
00:36:14,380 --> 00:36:17,175
If you don't cooperate,
I'll have to drag you out.

484
00:36:17,758 --> 00:36:18,968
Hello? Sir?

485
00:36:19,594 --> 00:36:20,928
I'll give you five seconds.

486
00:36:21,679 --> 00:36:23,723
Did you see that?

487
00:36:25,516 --> 00:36:26,767
I'll count to five.

488
00:36:27,602 --> 00:36:28,686
One,

489
00:36:28,769 --> 00:36:29,937
two,

490
00:36:30,521 --> 00:36:32,773
three, four.

491
00:36:32,857 --> 00:36:33,816
Stop counting.

492
00:36:43,034 --> 00:36:45,369
Let's go to the bathroom, sir. Get out.

493
00:36:46,829 --> 00:36:49,373
Your pants are wet, and it's cold.
You'll catch a cold.

494
00:36:50,499 --> 00:36:53,628
Let's get you changed,
and go someplace warm. It's cold here.

495
00:36:54,003 --> 00:36:54,962
Come along.

496
00:36:56,631 --> 00:36:57,632
Come along.

497
00:37:07,016 --> 00:37:08,434
It's cold. Let's go.

498
00:37:09,852 --> 00:37:11,062
It's so cold.

499
00:37:20,071 --> 00:37:21,072
He's mentally disabled.

500
00:37:21,697 --> 00:37:24,951
Consider this your good deed for the day,

501
00:37:25,618 --> 00:37:26,869
and wash your car with this.

502
00:37:30,665 --> 00:37:31,666
When you receive a call,

503
00:37:32,208 --> 00:37:35,920
calmly assess the situation first. How can
a cop lose her temper right off the bat?

504
00:37:36,921 --> 00:37:38,881
Couldn't you tell that he wasn't normal?

505
00:37:39,507 --> 00:37:41,676
His phone was around his neck,
his shoes were mismatched

506
00:37:41,759 --> 00:37:42,927
and he couldn't understand us.

507
00:37:43,386 --> 00:37:45,596
He was drooling too.
He's obviously not normal.

508
00:37:45,680 --> 00:37:47,682
We shouldn't use the term "not normal".

509
00:37:48,182 --> 00:37:50,810
We are able-bodied,
and he has disabilities.

510
00:37:51,644 --> 00:37:53,104
Those are the correct terms to use.

511
00:37:54,814 --> 00:37:56,023
How ignorant.

512
00:37:58,776 --> 00:38:02,905
Geez, at least she knows something.

513
00:38:27,638 --> 00:38:28,931
Dad, you're up?

514
00:38:30,516 --> 00:38:32,143
It's only 5 a.m.

515
00:38:32,226 --> 00:38:34,145
<i>I have a busy day ahead
with a lot of orders.</i>

516
00:38:35,563 --> 00:38:37,565
<i>Look at you. You're wearing your uniform.</i>

517
00:38:38,149 --> 00:38:39,608
Yes.

518
00:38:39,692 --> 00:38:42,153
Dad,
let me introduce you to my colleagues.

519
00:38:42,778 --> 00:38:46,407
This tall guy here lives downstairs
from me.

520
00:38:47,658 --> 00:38:51,829
This girl here is my roommate.
She can be a little standoffish.

521
00:38:53,873 --> 00:38:57,126
Dad, what's Mom doing now?
And what about Tae-yang and Hye-min?

522
00:38:57,209 --> 00:38:58,419
<i>They're still asleep.</i>

523
00:38:58,627 --> 00:39:00,755
<i>I have to work now. Let's talk later.</i>

524
00:39:01,172 --> 00:39:02,006
Yes, sir.

525
00:39:13,184 --> 00:39:15,353
Why didn't you say hello to my dad?

526
00:39:26,822 --> 00:39:29,075
I wasn't in the mood
to say hello to your dad.

527
00:39:30,034 --> 00:39:31,452
I didn't have dinner,

528
00:39:31,702 --> 00:39:33,829
my mentor made me park
the patrol car so he could sleep,

529
00:39:33,913 --> 00:39:35,039
and we have a ton of cases.

530
00:39:36,624 --> 00:39:38,626
All I do is issue tickets
for traffic violations.

531
00:39:40,211 --> 00:39:43,839
My mom, who has a panic disorder,
is ignoring my calls because she's mad.

532
00:39:48,052 --> 00:39:50,096
Seeing the homicide scene
must've been traumatizing.

533
00:39:52,223 --> 00:39:54,141
I've also seen a person covered in blood,

534
00:39:56,018 --> 00:39:57,686
so I know how traumatizing it can be.

535
00:39:59,563 --> 00:40:00,981
My dad is disabled.

536
00:40:02,149 --> 00:40:03,234
He lost a hand.

537
00:40:05,152 --> 00:40:06,570
I saw it happening.

538
00:40:11,575 --> 00:40:13,869
I'm sorry I said you're
calculating and obnoxious.

539
00:40:18,833 --> 00:40:19,917
See you in two days.

540
00:40:30,886 --> 00:40:31,762
How are you feeling?

541
00:40:33,722 --> 00:40:35,933
-I'm just...
-Just what? Tell me.

542
00:40:40,312 --> 00:40:41,313
To be honest,

543
00:40:42,648 --> 00:40:46,152
I think you'll scold me when you hear it
because you're so competent

544
00:40:46,652 --> 00:40:49,238
and you have varied experience
such as the Violent Crime Unit.

545
00:40:55,244 --> 00:40:56,912
But being a cop is scary.

546
00:41:02,751 --> 00:41:04,628
Today,
I issued traffic tickets all day long.

547
00:41:05,754 --> 00:41:09,258
I complained to Sergeant Kang and asked
why we didn't report to a case,

548
00:41:12,344 --> 00:41:14,180
but frankly, I had a relaxing day.

549
00:41:15,890 --> 00:41:16,974
Aren't I a total slacker?

550
00:41:18,434 --> 00:41:19,393
No.

551
00:41:22,229 --> 00:41:25,149
To tell you the truth,
homicide cases scare me as well.

552
00:41:25,900 --> 00:41:28,736
I'm sure that's how all cops feel
even though no one says it.

553
00:41:30,404 --> 00:41:31,780
Aren't I right?

554
00:41:32,114 --> 00:41:34,783
Chief and Captain,
isn't being a cop scary at times?

555
00:41:35,743 --> 00:41:37,745
No, I'm not scared.

556
00:41:38,746 --> 00:41:40,122
Why? Are you scared, Jeong-o?

557
00:41:40,206 --> 00:41:43,125
The solution is simple. Just quit.
How can you be a cop when you're scared?

558
00:41:44,251 --> 00:41:47,213
-Just go home and watch the kids.
-Goodness.

559
00:41:50,174 --> 00:41:52,968
He can be a jerk. That's just how he is.

560
00:41:55,679 --> 00:41:59,141
She needs some real consolation because of
the homicide case from the other day.

561
00:42:03,979 --> 00:42:05,773
What Captain Eun said isn't wrong.

562
00:42:08,192 --> 00:42:12,363
How can we call ourselves police officers
if we're scared of working on cases?

563
00:42:15,199 --> 00:42:16,700
Can I eat that if you don't want it?

564
00:42:28,796 --> 00:42:31,173
It's okay. You can be scared.

565
00:42:32,716 --> 00:42:35,928
But just remember this. Citizens can
avoid things when they're scared,

566
00:42:36,470 --> 00:42:39,974
but we, the police, must investigate
all cases even if we're scared.

567
00:42:41,141 --> 00:42:42,685
Just make a choice.

568
00:42:43,727 --> 00:42:45,187
Run away because you're scared,

569
00:42:45,771 --> 00:42:47,898
or look into the case
even though you're scared.

570
00:42:49,400 --> 00:42:50,317
What will you do?

571
00:43:01,287 --> 00:43:02,288
I still want to

572
00:43:04,039 --> 00:43:05,332
look into cases.

573
00:43:16,093 --> 00:43:19,763
It is scary. It sure is.

574
00:43:24,935 --> 00:43:25,978
This is hot.

575
00:43:27,938 --> 00:43:30,816
<i>Why won't you eat?
You worked hard all night.</i>

576
00:43:31,525 --> 00:43:33,235
I don't want to. I don't have an appetite.

577
00:43:34,445 --> 00:43:36,030
If you don't eat, I won't eat either.

578
00:44:00,971 --> 00:44:03,057
All right, I'm sorry. I'll eat.

579
00:44:03,182 --> 00:44:05,184
Get up already. Let's eat, okay?

580
00:44:06,101 --> 00:44:07,353
I don't want to eat.

581
00:44:08,270 --> 00:44:10,564
You said you haven't eaten
since your early morning shift.

582
00:44:10,981 --> 00:44:13,108
-What if you get sick?
-I'm sleepy.

583
00:44:13,233 --> 00:44:15,069
Leave me alone.
Eat something and go to bed.

584
00:44:16,528 --> 00:44:18,947
Don't fall asleep yet.
I'll go fix a meal for us.

585
00:45:09,331 --> 00:45:10,582
Mom.

586
00:45:11,625 --> 00:45:15,921
I cooked instant noodles.
Let's eat noodles.

587
00:45:17,840 --> 00:45:18,882
Sang-jun!

588
00:45:37,484 --> 00:45:39,611
Where did you get this?

589
00:45:39,695 --> 00:45:40,779
You don't need to know.

590
00:45:42,448 --> 00:45:44,408
Did your friend give it to you again?

591
00:45:45,284 --> 00:45:46,368
Yes.

592
00:45:47,119 --> 00:45:50,372
You little prick. You took money
from your friends again, didn't you?

593
00:45:50,456 --> 00:45:51,457
Yes, I did. So what?

594
00:45:52,124 --> 00:45:53,625
You punk.

595
00:45:53,709 --> 00:45:56,253
I'm going to teach you
a serious lesson today.

596
00:45:56,336 --> 00:45:59,173
You hit your friends
and take money from them every day.

597
00:45:59,256 --> 00:46:01,300
Did I teach you to do such bad things?
Did I?

598
00:46:01,383 --> 00:46:04,344
Then what am I supposed to do?
Both Sang-su and I are hungry.

599
00:46:04,595 --> 00:46:07,473
After Dad died, you don't cook for us.
All you do is drink.

600
00:46:07,556 --> 00:46:09,475
You're jobless, and you have no income!

601
00:46:09,558 --> 00:46:11,393
Is that your excuse
for acting like a punk?

602
00:46:12,478 --> 00:46:14,938
Why are you hitting me?
Who do you think you are?

603
00:46:15,439 --> 00:46:17,107
You have no right to hit us!

604
00:46:17,483 --> 00:46:19,943
You don't cook for us, you're jobless,
and all you do is drink!

605
00:46:20,444 --> 00:46:23,071
I hate you.
I'd much rather live in an orphanage.

606
00:46:23,655 --> 00:46:25,449
Send me and Sang-su to an orphanage.

607
00:46:25,949 --> 00:46:27,201
Send us to an orphanage!

608
00:46:32,080 --> 00:46:33,540
Sang-jun!

609
00:46:39,004 --> 00:46:40,088
That little jerk...

610
00:46:42,466 --> 00:46:43,592
I'm having a hard time too.

611
00:46:49,264 --> 00:46:51,475
You thought I wasn't going to eat, right?

612
00:46:52,184 --> 00:46:55,437
No, I knew that you were
trying to trick me to make me eat.

613
00:46:57,105 --> 00:47:00,150
You're such a good son.
I raised you so well.

614
00:47:00,651 --> 00:47:02,194
I don't like when you touch my head.

615
00:47:02,819 --> 00:47:03,904
Don't be so difficult.

616
00:47:11,578 --> 00:47:12,663
It's Sang-jun.

617
00:47:12,746 --> 00:47:14,998
I talked to him the other day.
You talk to him. I'm okay.

618
00:47:17,459 --> 00:47:18,752
Hey, Sang-jun. It's been a while.

619
00:47:28,595 --> 00:47:30,222
<i>I remember that day, of course.</i>

620
00:47:30,305 --> 00:47:32,516
<i>Had a cop like me caught you back then,</i>

621
00:47:32,599 --> 00:47:34,518
<i>you'd have ten counts of theft
on your record now.</i>

622
00:47:34,601 --> 00:47:35,852
<i>Stop making things up.</i>

623
00:47:35,936 --> 00:47:37,521
<i>I only did it twice.</i>

624
00:47:37,604 --> 00:47:38,939
<i>Only twice, my ass.</i>

625
00:47:39,064 --> 00:47:41,525
<i>I clearly remember
at least five incidents.</i>

626
00:47:41,650 --> 00:47:44,319
<i>That's not true. I was a good kid.</i>

627
00:47:46,154 --> 00:47:47,072
<i>You're right.</i>

628
00:47:48,031 --> 00:47:52,035
<i>So what's going to happen to that boy
from the Internet cafe?</i>

629
00:47:56,456 --> 00:47:57,457
<i>I don't know.</i>

630
00:47:58,709 --> 00:48:02,296
<i>I know there's nothing I can do,
but I can't stop worrying about him.</i>

631
00:48:03,463 --> 00:48:06,174
<i>I had you when our mom neglected us,</i>

632
00:48:07,009 --> 00:48:08,260
<i>but he's all alone.</i>

633
00:48:10,095 --> 00:48:11,763
<i>Children can't live alone.</i>

634
00:48:16,184 --> 00:48:18,437
-Pass the ball!
-Kick it over!

635
00:48:28,238 --> 00:48:29,448
Let's go!

636
00:48:31,116 --> 00:48:32,159
Nice pass.

637
00:48:41,209 --> 00:48:44,004
We should've gone to
a nice restaurant or coffee shop

638
00:48:44,087 --> 00:48:45,339
instead of staying home.

639
00:48:46,256 --> 00:48:48,634
Let's go out. It's even snowing outside.

640
00:49:03,148 --> 00:49:05,817
APPLICATION FOR DIVORCE
AND CUSTODY OF CHILDREN

641
00:49:16,411 --> 00:49:18,747
Next time, you bring the papers to me.

642
00:49:18,830 --> 00:49:20,040
I can't agree to a divorce.

643
00:49:21,124 --> 00:49:22,292
Take me to court.

644
00:49:23,293 --> 00:49:25,295
Just like the movie, <i>The War of the Roses</i>,

645
00:49:25,379 --> 00:49:27,631
we'll make a whole mess of things.
You and me. Shit.

646
00:49:44,690 --> 00:49:46,566
Not even a judge would understand this.

647
00:49:53,323 --> 00:49:54,324
Come on.

648
00:49:54,908 --> 00:49:56,326
What did I...

649
00:49:57,452 --> 00:49:58,829
What did I do that was so wrong?

650
00:50:00,372 --> 00:50:01,331
Did I hit you?

651
00:50:01,873 --> 00:50:03,500
Did I cheat on you?

652
00:50:03,917 --> 00:50:05,877
Or did I not provide for our family,
or was I--

653
00:50:06,169 --> 00:50:09,172
Just because you didn't hit me
or cheat on me,

654
00:50:09,423 --> 00:50:10,924
and you earned money for this family,

655
00:50:11,758 --> 00:50:13,635
doesn't mean that
I have to stay miserable.

656
00:50:13,719 --> 00:50:16,179
Can't you just let it slide?

657
00:50:16,513 --> 00:50:17,639
Why...

658
00:50:17,723 --> 00:50:20,267
Why is everything so complicated with you?

659
00:50:21,476 --> 00:50:23,645
I love you, and I'm happy.

660
00:50:23,729 --> 00:50:26,815
I don't love you, and I'm miserable.

661
00:51:03,226 --> 00:51:04,811
I thought that

662
00:51:05,854 --> 00:51:08,815
I'd need you desperately
at least once in my life.

663
00:51:09,524 --> 00:51:10,567
But it turns out

664
00:51:11,318 --> 00:51:12,402
that I didn't.

665
00:51:13,695 --> 00:51:16,823
I could do everything on my own,
without you.

666
00:51:18,700 --> 00:51:19,910
When I gave birth,

667
00:51:20,577 --> 00:51:21,745
when our kids were sick,

668
00:51:23,747 --> 00:51:28,627
when I took care of my parents,
who grew ill and collapsed

669
00:51:31,338 --> 00:51:32,714
after raising our kids for us,

670
00:51:34,007 --> 00:51:35,008
and

671
00:51:36,343 --> 00:51:37,719
their funeral.

672
00:51:39,805 --> 00:51:42,349
I was able to do all of it alone,
without you.

673
00:51:51,858 --> 00:51:52,901
Of course,

674
00:51:58,990 --> 00:52:02,202
it would've been nice to have you
by my side

675
00:52:04,329 --> 00:52:07,290
whenever I was scared, terrified,

676
00:52:07,916 --> 00:52:10,293
or desperate.

677
00:52:12,546 --> 00:52:13,588
However,

678
00:52:16,341 --> 00:52:18,635
you were never by my side. Not even once.

679
00:52:20,470 --> 00:52:21,596
You son of a bitch.

680
00:52:41,032 --> 00:52:42,450
I was working too.

681
00:52:45,412 --> 00:52:46,621
Jang-mi.

682
00:52:48,623 --> 00:52:50,000
I wasn't fooling around.

683
00:52:53,879 --> 00:52:54,921
Still...

684
00:52:57,799 --> 00:52:59,050
Still, I'm sorry.

685
00:53:00,427 --> 00:53:01,511
I really am.

686
00:53:07,601 --> 00:53:09,769
While I was scattering my parents' ashes,

687
00:53:11,646 --> 00:53:13,648
I let go of any fondness that

688
00:53:15,317 --> 00:53:16,276
I still had for you.

689
00:53:22,699 --> 00:53:24,534
I can't live with you anymore.

690
00:53:40,508 --> 00:53:42,552
I've been good to you until now, right?

691
00:53:43,511 --> 00:53:46,514
If that's the case, the least you can do
is give me this divorce.

692
00:54:07,452 --> 00:54:09,621
You may have been a crappy husband,

693
00:54:11,122 --> 00:54:13,166
but you are a great cop.

694
00:54:16,378 --> 00:54:17,587
What happened to Ho-cheol

695
00:54:19,881 --> 00:54:21,257
was just an accident.

696
00:54:24,803 --> 00:54:26,096
Why would you bring that up?

697
00:54:27,597 --> 00:54:29,432
If someone jumped into the ocean,

698
00:54:29,808 --> 00:54:33,478
even if he was a drunk,
you had to save him because you're a cop.

699
00:54:34,980 --> 00:54:37,983
You can't be responsible
for a freak accident.

700
00:54:38,483 --> 00:54:39,985
Cops are human too.

701
00:54:42,404 --> 00:54:43,655
I don't want you to feel guilty

702
00:54:45,115 --> 00:54:47,701
about what happened to Ho-cheol.

703
00:55:36,249 --> 00:55:37,709
Pass it here!

704
00:55:41,504 --> 00:55:42,547
Aren't you cold?

705
00:55:49,512 --> 00:55:53,892
Tomorrow, my mom is coming for me.

706
00:55:58,646 --> 00:56:01,149
Good for you. I'm glad she's coming.

707
00:56:01,733 --> 00:56:05,945
But I don't want to go to
the Internet cafe.

708
00:56:26,966 --> 00:56:28,051
Do you want it?

709
00:56:58,289 --> 00:56:59,707
Chew it 50 times.

710
00:57:11,886 --> 00:57:15,014
What? You gave the boy your business card?

711
00:57:18,601 --> 00:57:19,602
Geez.

712
00:57:23,773 --> 00:57:25,066
Do you think you're Superman?

713
00:57:26,276 --> 00:57:28,069
What can you do for him?

714
00:57:29,195 --> 00:57:31,573
Are you going to run to him when he calls?

715
00:57:31,656 --> 00:57:33,658
Or give him your monthly salary,
instead of your mom?

716
00:57:34,159 --> 00:57:35,869
What can you do for him?

717
00:57:37,370 --> 00:57:38,788
I won't do what I can't

718
00:57:38,872 --> 00:57:40,290
and do what I can.

719
00:57:41,624 --> 00:57:43,543
I can't stand doing nothing at all.

720
00:57:50,216 --> 00:57:51,551
I don't know about this.

721
00:58:07,901 --> 00:58:10,069
Hello, Captain An,
it's Yeom Sang-su from Hongil Patrol.

722
00:58:10,236 --> 00:58:11,988
About the video I sent you of the child...

723
00:58:12,071 --> 00:58:13,156
I showed it to her.

724
00:58:14,115 --> 00:58:16,159
I suggested she send the kid to a facility

725
00:58:16,242 --> 00:58:18,703
and get professional help herself.

726
00:58:18,786 --> 00:58:21,164
I even threatened to take her to court.

727
00:58:21,664 --> 00:58:22,665
But

728
00:58:23,917 --> 00:58:26,044
she'd rather die than give up her son.

729
00:58:27,045 --> 00:58:29,464
There's nothing
we can do to keep her here,

730
00:58:30,381 --> 00:58:31,841
<i>so we let her go.</i>

731
00:58:32,008 --> 00:58:34,135
<i>Prosecutors will indict her
for child neglect--</i>

732
00:58:34,219 --> 00:58:36,095
What if something goes wrong before then?

733
00:58:37,639 --> 00:58:39,933
If the mom's healthy,
then the kid's better off with her.

734
00:58:40,683 --> 00:58:43,770
But that woman needs help.
She's in no condition to raise a kid.

735
00:58:44,354 --> 00:58:46,314
<i>He'll have to fend for himself and he's</i>

736
00:58:47,315 --> 00:58:48,316
just a kid.

737
00:58:48,983 --> 00:58:50,860
-He can do nothing on his own.
-Silence.

738
00:58:51,861 --> 00:58:52,820
<i>I'll tell you clearly.</i>

739
00:58:54,030 --> 00:58:57,075
What you and I must do as a police officer

740
00:58:57,200 --> 00:58:58,826
ends as of this moment.

741
00:59:00,036 --> 00:59:01,829
<i>The instant this call ends,</i>

742
00:59:02,080 --> 00:59:03,957
<i>you should forget about
the Internet cafe kid.</i>

743
00:59:04,374 --> 00:59:08,336
Do not cling to this case. If not,
you won't be able to solve other cases.

744
00:59:49,377 --> 00:59:50,878
Hurry up.

745
00:59:50,962 --> 00:59:53,381
Hurry up. I need to get out.

746
00:59:53,464 --> 00:59:55,842
Hurry, hurry.

747
00:59:56,968 --> 00:59:59,596
Come up faster.

748
01:00:09,147 --> 01:00:10,523
Hello?

749
01:00:11,190 --> 01:00:13,067
Is this the police?

750
01:00:22,869 --> 01:00:24,996
Who turns the siren on in an emergency?

751
01:00:25,121 --> 01:00:27,248
The perp could get away if he's nearby.

752
01:00:27,332 --> 01:00:29,792
Don't you know protocol?
Turn the siren off.

753
01:00:32,962 --> 01:00:34,547
Turn your hazard lights on.

754
01:00:39,427 --> 01:00:40,678
Myeong-ho, where are you?

755
01:00:42,597 --> 01:00:44,641
I checked the security footage
from nearby.

756
01:00:44,724 --> 01:00:46,225
Thanks for your help.

757
01:00:47,602 --> 01:00:49,187
We'll go to where the woman disappeared.

758
01:00:49,270 --> 01:00:51,314
It's a blind spot,
so we can't see anything.

759
01:00:51,397 --> 01:00:52,940
We'll arrive at the scene soon.

760
01:00:53,941 --> 01:00:57,487
It has only been ten minutes
since the call came in.

761
01:00:57,779 --> 01:00:59,781
In that time,
she couldn't have gotten far.

762
01:00:59,989 --> 01:01:01,157
Okay.

763
01:01:07,955 --> 01:01:10,083
I see Captain Eun is already here.

764
01:01:41,239 --> 01:01:42,490
You're here early.

765
